110.3	Jiddu_Krishnamurti	Jiddu Krishnamurti	Jiddu Krishnamurti (Telugu: ; May 12, 1895 â€“ February 17, 1986) or J. Krishnamurti (Telugu: ) was an Indian writer and speaker on philosophical and spiritual subjects. His subject matter included: psychological revolution, the nature of the mind, meditation, human relationships, and bringing about positive change in society. He constantly stressed the need for a revolution in the psyche of every human being and emphasized that such revolution cannot be brought about by any external entity, be it religious, political, or social.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/Jiddu_Krishnamurti_01.jpg/250px-Jiddu_Krishnamurti_01.jpg
